KABOKWENI-  According to White River Police Flying Squad Leader, Capt Pieter Smit, the men were armed with AK-47’s. “Security staff were ordered to lie down. The suspects had female capes and dresses on. So when they entered the premises it looked like they were old grandmothers. About R500 000 pension money that was still in the boxes, which the suspects took.” He said the suspects fled in a vehicle from the scene. “No shots were fired, no security were robbed of their firearms and nobody was injured.”
Police are still searching the surrounding area for the suspects.